# Docker build context exclusions.
#
# None of the apps/*/Dockerfiles had a .dockerignore before this — every
# `docker build ... .` sent the ENTIRE repo (including node_modules,
# .git, dist/, build artifacts) as build context. Worse than the size
# cost: `COPY apps/<app> apps/<app>` in each Dockerfile copies a local
# node_modules straight into the image AFTER the container's own `pnpm
# install` already ran, silently overwriting the correctly-linked
# in-container install with whatever happens to be on the build
# machine's disk (wrong platform's native bindings, stale symlinks,
# missing packages). Confirmed reproducing this exact failure locally
# for apps/web-next's astro binary — builds fine from a clean checkout
# (e.g. a fresh CI runner), breaks silently on any machine with a local
# node_modules already installed.

node_modules
**/node_modules

.git
.github

# Build output — Dockerfiles build fresh, never consume host-built dist/.
dist
**/dist
apps/*/dist
apps/storybook/storybook-static

# Test artifacts / local-only state.
apps/e2e/uat-results
apps/e2e/test-results
apps/e2e/playwright-report
coverage
**/coverage

# Editor / tool directories not needed at build time.
.vscode
.idea
.kilo
.kilocode
.copilot
.claude

# Env files — never bake secrets into an image; Dockerfiles that need
# runtime env get it via `environment:`/`env_file:` in compose, not COPY.
.env
.env.*
